My research interests are quite broad spanning from general
theoretical condensed matter physics (including DFT and Green's functions)
to quantum chemistry and theory
of AFM and MIES. Specifically, a lot of effort I have been putting into the theory
of cluster embedding where I have been trying to derive the embedding potential
and interaction in the environment region  using the 
Arrow Diagram Thechnique within the Theory of Electronic Separability. 
Presently, I am involved in an EPSRS funded project which focuses
radiative/non-radiative transitions in surface point defects under the AFM tip.
